#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn4:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn4:0.2"
msgid "Bhayabheravasutta "
msgstr "Fear and Dread "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli1.17, sc1
msgctxt "mn4:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn4:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn4:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

#. VAR: sāraṇīyaṃ → sārāṇīyaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn4:2.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha: "

# NOTE: Bodhi, Nyanamoli, and Thanissaro translate this as a question. However, there are none of the usual question markers and given the varied sequence as evident in the EA version (see Analayo) it seems likely that Horner was right to translate as a statement.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: samādapetā → samādāpetā (?)
msgctxt "mn4:2.3"
msgid "“yeme, bho gotama, kulaputtā bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ uddissa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, bhavaṃ tesaṃ gotamo pubbaṅgamo, bhavaṃ tesaṃ gotamo bahukāro, bhavaṃ tesaṃ gotamo samādapetā; "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, those gentlemen who have gone forth from the lay life to homelessness out of faith in Master Gotama have Master Gotama to lead the way, help them out, and give them encouragement. "

msgctxt "mn4:2.4"
msgid "bhoto ca pana gotamassa sā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "And those people follow Master Gotama’s example.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn4:2.5"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa, evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, brahmin! Everything you say is true, brahmin!” "

msgctxt "mn4:2.6"
msgid "Ye te, brāhmaṇa, kulaputtā mamaṃ uddissa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, ahaṃ tesaṃ pubbaṅgamo, ahaṃ tesaṃ bahukāro, ahaṃ tesaṃ samādapetā; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn4:2.7"
msgid "mama ca pana sā janatā diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjatī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Note that BB renders this phrase differently here and at AN 10.99
msgctxt "mn4:2.8"
msgid "“Durabhisambhavāni hi kho, bho gotama, araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni, dukkaraṃ pavivekaṃ, durabhiramaṃ "
msgstr "“But Master Gotama, remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest are challenging. It’s hard to maintain seclusion and hard to find joy in it. "

msgctxt "mn4:2.9"
msgid "ekatte, haranti maññe mano vanāni samādhiṃ alabhamānassa bhikkhuno”ti. "
msgstr "Staying alone, the forests seem to rob the mind of a mendicant who isn’t immersed in samādhi.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn4:2.10"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa, evametaṃ, brāhmaṇa. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, brahmin! Everything you say is true, brahmin! "

msgctxt "mn4:2.11"
msgid "Durabhisambhavāni hi kho, brāhmaṇa, araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni, dukkaraṃ pavivekaṃ, durabhiramaṃ ekatte, haranti maññe mano vanāni samādhiṃ alabhamānassa bhikkhuno. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc2
msgctxt "mn4:3.1"
msgid "Mayhampi kho, brāhmaṇa, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi: "
msgstr "Before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I too thought, "

msgctxt "mn4:3.2"
msgid "‘durabhisambhavāni hi kho araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni, dukkaraṃ pavivekaṃ, durabhiramaṃ "
msgstr "‘Remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest are challenging. It’s hard to maintain seclusion, and hard to find joy in it. "

msgctxt "mn4:3.3"
msgid "ekatte, haranti maññe mano vanāni samādhiṃ alabhamānassa bhikkhuno’ti. "
msgstr "Staying alone, the forests seem to rob the mind of a mendicant who isn’t immersed in samādhi.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4
msgctxt "mn4:4.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "mn4:4.2"
msgid "‘ye kho keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā aparisuddhakāyakammantā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, aparisuddhakāyakammantasandosahetu have te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā akusalaṃ bhayabheravaṃ avhāyanti. "
msgstr "‘There are ascetics and brahmins with unpurified conduct of body, speech, and mind who frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. Those ascetics and brahmins summon unskillful fear and dread because of these defects in their conduct. "

msgctxt "mn4:4.3"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ aparisuddhakāyakammanto araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevāmi; "
msgstr "But I don’t frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest with unpurified conduct of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "mn4:4.4"
msgid "parisuddhakāyakammantohamasmi. "
msgstr "My conduct is purified. "

msgctxt "mn4:4.5"
msgid "Ye hi vo ariyā parisuddhakāyakammantā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti tesamahaṃ aññataro’ti. "
msgstr "I am one of those noble ones who frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest with purified conduct of body, speech, and mind.’ "

msgctxt "mn4:4.6"
msgid "Etamahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, parisuddhakāyakammataṃ attani sampassamāno bhiyyo pallomamāpādiṃ araññe vihārāya. (1) "
msgstr "Seeing this purity of conduct in myself I felt even more unruffled about staying in the forest. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5-7, sc3
msgctxt "mn4:5-7.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "mn4:5-7.2"
msgid "‘ye kho keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā aparisuddhavacīkammantā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn4:5-7.3"
msgid "aparisuddhamanokammantā … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn4:5-7.4"
msgid "aparisuddhājīvā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, aparisuddhājīvasandosahetu have te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā akusalaṃ bhayabheravaṃ avhāyanti. "
msgstr "‘There are ascetics and brahmins with unpurified livelihood who frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest. Those ascetics and brahmins summon unskillful fear and dread because of these defects in their livelihood. "

msgctxt "mn4:5-7.5"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ aparisuddhājīvo araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevāmi; "
msgstr "But I don’t frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest with unpurified livelihood. "

msgctxt "mn4:5-7.6"
msgid "parisuddhājīvohamasmi. "
msgstr "My livelihood is purified. "

msgctxt "mn4:5-7.7"
msgid "Ye hi vo ariyā parisuddhājīvā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti tesamahaṃ aññataro’ti. "
msgstr "I am one of those noble ones who frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest with purified livelihood.’ "

msgctxt "mn4:5-7.8"
msgid "Etamahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, parisuddhājīvataṃ attani sampassamāno bhiyyo pallomamāpādiṃ araññe vihārāya. (2–4.) "
msgstr "Seeing this purity of livelihood in myself I felt even more unruffled about staying in the forest. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli1.18, sc4
msgctxt "mn4:8.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "mn4:8.2"
msgid "‘ye kho keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā abhijjhālū kāmesu tibbasārāgā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, abhijjhālukāmesutibbasārāgasandosahetu have te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā akusalaṃ bhayabheravaṃ avhāyanti. "
msgstr "‘There are ascetics and brahmins full of desire for sensual pleasures, with acute lust … "

msgctxt "mn4:8.3"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ abhijjhālu kāmesu tibbasārāgo araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevāmi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn4:8.4"
msgid "anabhijjhālūhamasmi. "
msgstr "I am not full of desire …’ "

msgctxt "mn4:8.5"
msgid "Ye hi vo ariyā anabhijjhālū araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti, tesamahaṃ aññataro’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn4:8.6"
msgid "Etamahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, anabhijjhālutaṃ attani sampassamāno bhiyyo pallomamāpādiṃ araññe vihārāya. (5) "
msgstr " "

